## 12. Design Decisions (Resolved)

| ID | Question | Decision | Rationale |
|----|----------|----------|-----------|
| Q1 | Profile completeness: percentage vs prompt card? | **Simple prompt card** | Less cognitive load, cleaner premium aesthetic, avoids gamification. Industry standard (Twitter/X, Instagram). |
| Q2 | Incomplete profile prompt dismissibility? | **Temporarily (7 days)** | Balances user autonomy with gentle re-engagement. Permanent dismissal risks incomplete profiles forever. |
| Q3 | Preview mode in Edit Profile? | **No** | Form fields show real-time input; avatar has upload preview. Adding preview adds complexity without clear value for simple text fields. |
| Q4 | Allow handle/username changes? | **No (immutable)** | Per architecture decision. Prevents URL breakage, identity confusion, and simplifies system. Support contact for exceptional cases. |
| Q5 | Location field autocomplete? | **No for MVP** | Requires geocoding API, adds scope. Free-text sufficient for MVP. Can be enhanced in future iteration. |

